com.supenta.flitchio.sdk

Class Status

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.supenta.flitchio.sdk.Status
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Status.FailingStatus

    public class Status
extends Object
    Object describing the status of a FlitchioController. You can query a controller for its status with FlitchioController.getStatus(), and you can get notified of status changes by implementing a FlitchioStatusListener and passing it to FlitchioController.onCreate(FlitchioStatusListener).
    Since:
    0.7.0

      • BINDING_FAILED

        public static final int BINDING_FAILED
        The FlitchioController couldn't bind to the Flitchio Manager app, or the previous binding has ended unexpectedly. A status with this code is a Status.FailingStatus and it holds a reason for the failure in Status.failureReason.

      • CONNECTED

        public static final int CONNECTED
        The FlitchioController is bound to the Flitchio Manager app and Flitchio is connected to the phone. You can call FlitchioController.obtainSnapshot() to poll data. You will also start getting event callbacks if you have declared a FlitchioEventListener.

      • code

        public final int code

      • failureReason

        public final int failureReason
        If this status' Status.code is Status.BINDING_FAILED, this holds the reason of the failure and its value is either one of Status.FailingStatus.REASON_MANAGER_UNUSABLE, Status.FailingStatus.REASON_SERVICE_REFUSED_CONNECTION, Status.FailingStatus.REASON_SERVICE_UNREACHABLE or Status.FailingStatus.REASON_SERVICE_SHUTDOWN_CONNECTION. If this status' Status.code is not Status.BINDING_FAILED, its value is Status.FailingStatus.NOT_FAILED.
        Since:
        0.7.0
